  "why": "The paper proposes a method for 'regression fuzzing', which is designed to find faults that are introduced during the evolution of a Deep Learning (DL) model. The entire methodology and evaluation focus on finding inputs that are correctly classified by a prior version of a model (M1) but are misclassified by its subsequent version (M2). The experiments are conducted on pairs of models where M2 is derived directly from M1 through processes like fine-tuning or pruning. The paper does not investigate whether the fault-inducing inputs discovered for a specific M1-M2 pair can also trigger failures in other, independently trained models. The concept of cross-model attack transferability is neither a design goal nor an evaluated property of the proposed DRFuzz method.",
